An HTTP/1.0 service that serves a single static HTML file. The file
path is declared in the source as a resource — the binary cannot
serve any other file because there is no syntax for runtime path
selection. Every request gets the same file; status is computed from
the request method (GET → 200, anything else → 405).

The file is read from disk on every accept loop iteration, so an
operator can update /tmp/verbose_static_index.html and the next
request sees the new content (no recompile, no signal). If the file
becomes unreadable mid-flight (deleted, permission revoked) the
process exits with status 1 — the on_read_error: abort policy makes
"silently serving stale content" impossible.

This is the smallest demonstrable static file server in Verbose: one
file, one route, one binary, full audit story.
